  encounter_id STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"encounter_id\" field uniquely identifies an encounter within a healthcare system. It is crucial for linking related data across different systems and ensuring continuity of care. This identifier is typically assigned by the healthcare provider\'s system and is used to track the patient\'s interactions with healthcare services. It is essential for data integration, reporting, and analytics, allowing for accurate retrieval and association of encounter-related information.'),
  lastupdated TIMESTAMP OPTIONS(description='The \"lastupdated\" field indicates the most recent date and time when the encounter record was modified. This timestamp is vital for data synchronization and version control, ensuring that the most current information is available across systems. It helps in maintaining data integrity and is used in auditing processes to track changes over time. Accurate timestamps are crucial for clinical decision-making and operational efficiency.'),
  hl7_message_date_time STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"hl7_message_date_time\" field represents the date and time when the HL7 message related to the encounter was generated. This field is important for message tracking and processing, ensuring timely communication between systems. It helps in understanding the sequence of events and is used in troubleshooting and auditing to verify message delivery and processing times.'),
  hl7_message_date_time_UTC TIMESTAMP OPTIONS(description='The \"hl7_message_date_time_UTC\" field provides the date and time of the HL7 message in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). This standardization is crucial for interoperability across different time zones, ensuring consistent interpretation of message timestamps. It aids in global data exchange and is essential for systems that operate across multiple regions, facilitating accurate synchronization and analysis.'),
  hl7_message_control_id STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"hl7_message_control_id\" field is a unique identifier for an HL7 message, used to track and manage message exchanges. It ensures message integrity and is critical for acknowledging receipt and processing of messages. This identifier helps in preventing duplicate processing and is essential for troubleshooting communication issues between systems, providing a reference point for message audits.'),
  meta_latest_source_date_time STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"meta_latest_source_date_time\" field indicates the most recent date and time when the source data for the encounter was updated. This field is important for data provenance and ensures that the latest information is being used for clinical and operational purposes. It helps in tracking data lineage and is crucial for maintaining data accuracy and reliability across systems.'),
  intermediate_snapshot_creation_date_time STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"intermediate_snapshot_creation_date_time\" field records the date and time when an intermediate snapshot of the encounter data was created. This snapshot is used for data backup, recovery, and analysis, providing a point-in-time view of the data. It is essential for ensuring data consistency and is used in scenarios where data needs to be restored or compared over time.'),
  final_fhir_write_date_time STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"final_fhir_write_date_time\" field represents the date and time when the encounter data was last written to the FHIR server. This timestamp is crucial for ensuring that the most recent data is available for clinical use and interoperability. It helps in tracking data updates and is essential for maintaining data accuracy and consistency across FHIR implementations.'),
  final_fhir_commit_date_time TIMESTAMP OPTIONS(description='The \"final_fhir_commit_date_time\" field indicates the date and time when the encounter data was committed to the FHIR server. This timestamp is important for ensuring data integrity and consistency, marking the point at which data changes become permanent. It is used in auditing and version control, providing a reliable reference for data updates and ensuring accurate data representation.'),
  encounter_version_id STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"encounter_version_id\" field uniquely identifies a specific version of an encounter record. This versioning is crucial for tracking changes over time and ensuring that the correct data is used in clinical and operational processes. It supports data integrity and is essential for auditing, allowing for the retrieval of historical data and understanding the evolution of an encounter.'),
  version_id_fingerprint INTEGER OPTIONS(description='The \'version_id_fingerprint\' field is used to uniquely identify a specific version of the Encounter resource. It ensures data integrity and version control, allowing systems to track changes and updates to the encounter information. This is crucial for maintaining accurate and up-to-date patient records, especially in environments where data is frequently updated or exchanged. The fingerprint is typically generated using a hash function, providing a compact and unique representation of the version.'),
  consent_coid STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'consent_coid\' field represents the consent identifier associated with the encounter. It is crucial for managing patient consent for data sharing and treatment, ensuring compliance with legal and ethical standards. This identifier links the encounter to specific consent records, facilitating the enforcement of patient preferences regarding data use and disclosure. Proper management of consent information is essential for protecting patient privacy and supporting informed decision-making.'),
  meta_action_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'meta_action_code\' field indicates the type of action performed on the Encounter resource, such as creation, update, or deletion. This field is vital for audit trails and data management, allowing systems to track changes and maintain a history of actions taken on the resource. Understanding the action code helps in synchronizing data across systems and ensuring that the most current and accurate information is available for clinical and administrative purposes.'),
  hl7_v2_source_interface STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'hl7_v2_source_interface\' field identifies the source interface from which the HL7 v2 message originated. This is important for interoperability and data integration, as it helps systems understand the context and origin of the data. Knowing the source interface can aid in troubleshooting, data validation, and ensuring that the data is correctly interpreted and processed by receiving systems. It plays a key role in maintaining data consistency across different healthcare systems.'),
  patient_account_num STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'patient_account_num\' field represents the unique account number assigned to the patient for billing and administrative purposes. It is essential for linking encounters to financial records, facilitating billing processes, and ensuring accurate reimbursement. This identifier helps healthcare providers manage patient accounts, track services rendered, and maintain financial records. Proper management of patient account numbers is crucial for operational efficiency and financial integrity in healthcare settings.'),
  patient_primary_id STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'patient_primary_id\' field is a unique identifier for the patient, used to link the encounter to the patient\'s medical record. It is critical for ensuring that the encounter data is accurately associated with the correct patient, supporting continuity of care and clinical decision-making. This identifier helps prevent errors in patient identification, which can lead to serious clinical and administrative consequences. It is a fundamental element in maintaining accurate and reliable patient records.'),
  network_mnemonic STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'network_mnemonic\' field is a shorthand identifier for the healthcare network associated with the encounter. It is used to categorize and manage encounters within a specific network, facilitating data organization and reporting. This field helps in understanding the context of the encounter, such as the network\'s policies, practices, and resources. Proper use of network mnemonics supports efficient data management and enhances the ability to analyze and improve healthcare delivery across networks.'),
  medical_record_num STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'medical_record_num\' field is a unique identifier for the patient\'s medical record, linking the encounter to the patient\'s comprehensive health history. It is crucial for accessing and updating the patient\'s medical information, supporting clinical care, and ensuring continuity of care. This identifier helps healthcare providers quickly retrieve relevant patient data, facilitating informed clinical decision-making and efficient care delivery. Accurate management of medical record numbers is essential for maintaining high-quality patient records.'),
  coid STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'coid\' field represents a unique identifier for the encounter, often used for internal tracking and management purposes. It is essential for distinguishing between different encounters, supporting data organization, and facilitating efficient retrieval and analysis of encounter information. This identifier helps ensure that each encounter is accurately recorded and managed, contributing to effective clinical and administrative operations. Proper use of encounter identifiers is crucial for maintaining data integrity and supporting healthcare delivery.'),
  facility_mnemonic STRING OPTIONS(description='The \'facility_mnemonic\' field is a shorthand identifier for the healthcare facility where the encounter took place. It is used to categorize and manage encounters by facility, supporting data organization and reporting. This field helps in understanding the context of the encounter, such as the facility\'s resources, practices, and policies. Proper use of facility mnemonics enhances data management and supports the analysis and improvement of healthcare delivery at the facility level.'),
  fhir_visit_status STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"fhir_visit_status\" field in a FHIR Encounter resource indicates the current status of the encounter, such as planned, in-progress, or completed. It is crucial for tracking the encounter\'s lifecycle and managing workflows. This status helps in understanding the patient\'s current interaction with the healthcare system and is essential for operational management, resource allocation, and care coordination. Accurate status reporting ensures effective communication among healthcare providers and supports timely decision-making.'),
  fhir_patient_class_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"fhir_patient_class_code\" field represents the classification of the patient during the encounter, such as inpatient, outpatient, or emergency. This classification is vital for determining the level of care, resource allocation, and billing processes. It helps in understanding the context of the encounter and is used for reporting and analytics. Accurate patient class coding is essential for compliance with healthcare regulations and for optimizing care delivery.'),
  fhir_patient_class_display STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"fhir_patient_class_display\" field provides a human-readable description of the patient class code, such as \'Inpatient\' or \'Outpatient\'. This field enhances the interpretability of the patient class code, facilitating better communication among healthcare providers and stakeholders. It is useful for user interfaces and reports where a clear understanding of the patient\'s classification is necessary. Consistent and accurate display values support effective clinical and administrative workflows.'),
  patient_type STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"patient_type\" field categorizes the patient based on specific criteria, such as new or established patient, or based on the type of care being provided. This classification aids in tailoring care plans, managing resources, and optimizing scheduling. It is also used in reporting and analytics to understand patient demographics and care patterns. Accurate patient type classification is crucial for personalized care delivery and efficient healthcare operations.'),
  admission_type STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"admission_type\" field indicates the nature of the patient\'s admission, such as elective, emergency, or urgent. This information is critical for prioritizing care, managing hospital resources, and planning treatment strategies. It also plays a role in billing and reimbursement processes. Understanding the admission type helps in assessing the urgency of care and aligning healthcare services with patient needs. Accurate admission type coding supports effective clinical and operational decision-making.'),
  patient_class_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"patient_class_code\" field specifies the classification of the patient during the encounter, similar to \"fhir_patient_class_code\". It is used to categorize the encounter context, such as inpatient or outpatient, and is essential for billing, resource management, and care coordination. Accurate patient class coding ensures compliance with healthcare standards and supports efficient healthcare delivery. It is a key element in understanding the scope and nature of the encounter.'),
  account_status_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"account_status_code\" field represents the current status of the patient\'s account, such as active, inactive, or closed. This status is important for financial management, billing processes, and ensuring accurate record-keeping. It helps in tracking the financial aspects of the patient\'s care and supports revenue cycle management. Accurate account status coding is crucial for maintaining financial integrity and ensuring compliance with healthcare financial regulations.'),
  vip_indicator_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"vip_indicator_code\" field identifies whether the patient is considered a VIP (Very Important Person) within the healthcare setting. This designation may affect the level of service, privacy considerations, and resource allocation. It is important for managing patient expectations and ensuring appropriate care delivery. Accurate VIP coding helps in providing personalized care and maintaining patient satisfaction, while also ensuring that healthcare resources are used effectively.'),
  financial_class_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"financial_class_code\" field categorizes the patient\'s financial responsibility or insurance coverage, such as self-pay, insured, or government program. This classification is crucial for billing, reimbursement, and financial planning. It helps in understanding the patient\'s financial obligations and supports revenue cycle management. Accurate financial class coding ensures compliance with healthcare financial regulations and optimizes the billing process, contributing to the financial health of the healthcare organization.'),
