  accommodation_code_category STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"accommodation_code_category\" field categorizes the type of accommodation provided during an encounter. It provides a higher-level classification than the specific accommodation code, helping in reporting and analysis. This categorization aids in understanding the general type of accommodation, such as \'private\', \'semi-private\', or \'ward\', and is useful for operational and financial management.'),
  hospital_service_type_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"hospital_service_type_code\" field identifies the specific type of service provided during the encounter, such as surgery, maternity, or emergency services. This code is crucial for clinical documentation, billing, and resource allocation. It is typically derived from a standardized code set to ensure interoperability and accurate reporting across healthcare systems.'),
  hospital_service_type_text STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"hospital_service_type_text\" field provides a human-readable description of the service type provided during the encounter. It complements the \"hospital_service_type_code\" by offering a textual representation, which is useful for clinical documentation and communication among healthcare providers. This field enhances understanding and clarity in patient records.'),
  admit_source_code STRING OPTIONS(description='The \"admit_source_code\" field indicates the source from which the patient was admitted to the healthcare facility, such as a physician referral, emergency room, or transfer from another facility. This information is vital for understanding patient flow, resource planning, and care coordination. It is typically coded using a standardized system to ensure consistency and interoperability.'),
